This is my second map ever and my first bomb/defuse map. Hope you enjoy. ---------------
- Concept: When I decided to create this map, my original idea was based on a previous map that I started a few years ago but never finnished. It had some mystic purple & blue lights inside some buildings that resembled a sacred place. It was getting really cool but unfortunnately I never had the patience to finnish it. So I started this map with that idea in mind, but I was also inspired by the de.Dust map's environment and I actually started by recreating Dust's Terrorists spawn (wich now has turned into a bombsite). Then, as the map advanced and I chose some textures for the walls, it started to remind me of de.Aztec. I liked it and so I decided that the theme of de.Naga would be inspired on that map while the colors and ambience would be inspired in de.Dust and in my old map. Then I had to get really creative in order to solve some structural problems and later on I added some details like pyramids, water, wood, debris, etc... Originally, de.Naga only had 2 routes - one for each bombsite - but I thought it was too straight forward and so I decided to add a third route - wich is a middle route that links both bombsites - and it added a little more strategy to the map. Later on, and when the map was ready for the final stage of creation, I decided to change almost all the texturing (only the dust floor remained unchanged), to create another area and to move the bombsite A there. Then, when I finally decided it was done I started creating the 3D skybox (wich is done) and I tried to create a Radar Overview but had some problems doing it and so I decided not to include it on this version. Maybe I'll try to do it again when I port (if I do so) this map to CS - Global Ofensive. So, de.Naga has a common concept (because there's a lot of maps with a "de.Aztec meets de.Dust" ambience) but with some original details. --------------- FINAL VERSION RELEASED! Download Note: If you have downloaded an alpha or beta version, you should download again - the FINAL version is out now. ------------------ Thanks! Janus

"DE_Museum is a totally new CS:Source version of my popular CS map de_museum. This is not a conversion of the old CS map. This is a ground-up, from scratch reconstruction for the source engine.

Features:
-Fully modeled dinosaur skeletons including T. rex and Brachiosaurus
-Both skeletons are climbable (and explode with bomb detonation)
-Many more custom models and textures.
-Richly detailed architecture.
-Vents now give access to ceiling in T. rex room.
-New, more balanced layout.
-CT/T sniper windows guard primary choke point.
-Actual museum exhibits.
-Beta has generic nav.
-40 spawn points"

de_motel_b4 has been released! ------ Third Version of de_motel, once a cs_map. It turned out that most of the time the bombb was planted at A and not at B. I tried to make bomb spot B more interesting and gave more options to approach it: I added -truck added for more cover -stairs from the floor of Cafe Baltic to B -ladder at one of the trucks, you can use to get to the roof of B -a second ladder to the quadratic roof -ladder at the staircase to the roof -moved van, so you can get through at bove sides Further changes: -created a real pool at A. Players can stand in the water. Bomb can be planted underwater. By ducking you may try to hide underwater. -created a hole in the red roof -used playerclip to avoid that players get stuck -many optimizations (changing passable appartments, so you can't look through; removed the most unnecessary appartments) -few details added. -includes 2*64 spawnpoints

cs_motel by Soctom turned into a de-scenario. In the second beta there is another ladder to the B-roof and the "Cafe Baltic" is now passable. The map includes a radar. De_monte

Map by kaka

Nav file by chizbone

In a almost completely abandoned village...

A mining company linked with the mafia believes the area under the village to be a big mining prospect. But a few of the locals refuse to sell there land.
The company decides to hire terrorists to try to scare the last remaing villagers off by blowing up one of the village's two statues. 
The police gets a tip of the attempt and arrives at the same time...


My focus was on the maps gameplay. I wanted to make a map that are both well balanced and fun to play.
